File: Eskom has implemented power cuts. Unsplash/Johannes Plenio JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has suspended power cuts from midday on Saturday as generation capacity recovers after initially the power cuts were meant to last till Monday. READ: Eskom, SOEs to look into scrapyard policy change The power utility says the system has recovered and that emergency reserves have been adequately replenished. Units at Matla, Majuba, Grootvlei and Kendal power stations have returned to service. Last night blackouts were reduced to stage one. Eskom says although the generators have been restored there's an increased demand for electricity as winter looms. Consumers are being urged to use power sparingly. 